<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-11-16T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-11-16T20:00:00-05:00" n="750" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d750">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">124.93/377: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-11-16T20:00:00-05:00">November 16, 1937—8
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>357. Your 920, November 16, 2 p.m. and 922, November 16, 4 p.m.</p>
                            <p>In the event that the Government removes to Hankow or to a point
                                inland you should follow the Government as far as Hankow. In making
                                your arrangements for this move as well as for leaving members <pb facs="0690" n="683" xml:id="pg_683"/> of the staff at Nanking
                                you should insofar as practicable concert your action with that of
                                the diplomatic representatives of other principally interested
                                Governments.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>